      <intermediateExchange id="4aad949d-55aa-5554-8573-cd7819ffbb03" unitId="980b811e-3905-4797-82a5-173f5568bc7e" amount="0.22" intermediateExchangeId="63ead738-2005-498c-8359-7f65c134a1a4" activityLinkId="8a4d3237-2b7f-52c5-af32-a08b2c4ed324">
        <name xml:lang="en">heat, from steam, in chemical industry</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">MJ</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This value is estimated based on the heating requirements of a similar process. Specifically, this value represents the hydrogenation of benzene, which was reported by Chauvel, Alain, Gilles Lefebvre, and L. Castex in "Petrochemical processes. Technical and economical characteristics Vol. 2." (1989) for the liquid phase process in presence of Raney nickel catalyst. The steam input of 0.08 kg per kg are required at medium pressure, while low pressure steam is go-generated amounting to 0.95 kg per kg that could potentially recovered. All in all, we assume that the heating requirements for the hydrogenation of toluene and benzene are similar.</comment>
        <uncertainty>
          <lognormal meanValue="0.22" mu="-1.5141277326297755" variance="0.0006" varianceWithPedigreeUncertainty="0.006"/>
          <pedigreeMatrix reliability="2" completeness="4" temporalCorrelation="2" geographicalCorrelation="5" furtherTechnologyCorrelation="2"/>
        </uncertainty>
