      <elementaryExchange id="7c217841-5f4b-531d-9ab7-4071e2a25b2c" unitId="de5b3c87-0e35-4fb0-9765-4f3ba34c99e5" variableName="CW_u" casNumber="007732-18-5" amount="0.0031217570685" isCalculatedAmount="true" mathematicalRelation="0.891930591 * ( 3.5 / 1000 )" elementaryExchangeId="fc1c42ce-a759-49fa-b987-f1ec5e503db1" formula="H2O">
        <name xml:lang="en">Water, cooling, unspecified natural origin</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">m3</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">This value is estimated based on the cooling requirements of a similar process. Specifically, this value represents the hydrogenation of benzene, which was reported by Chauvel, Alain, Gilles Lefebvre, and L. Castex in "Petrochemical processes. Technical and economical characteristics Vol. 2." (1989). The value of cooling water input for the latter process is 0.0035 m3 per kg.

At the same time, the latter amount was split between the following sources (1) "Water, cooling, unspecified natural origin", (2) "Water, river", and (3) "Water, well. in ground"</comment>
